<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.sheilaomalley.com/archives/001033.html" class="external text" title="http://www.sheilaomalley.com/archives/001033.html" rel="nofollow">The Sheila Variations: Jefferson and Locke</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Stephen J. McNamee and Robert K. Miller, Jr., <i>[The Meritocracy Myth <a href="http://www.rowmanlittlefield.com/isbn/0742510565" class="external free" title="http://www.rowmanlittlefield.com/isbn/0742510565" rel="nofollow">http://www.rowmanlittlefield.com/isbn/0742510565</a>]</i> (Rowman &amp; Littlefield, 2004); see also <a href="http://www.ncsociology.org/sociationtoday/v21/merit.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ncsociology.org/sociationtoday/v21/merit.htm" rel="nofollow">the authors' summary</a></li>
